<TITLE> Farmer slaughtered in sleep </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, May 22 (bdnews24.com)  A farmer was slaughtered by criminals in Nimtali village of Dhunat upazila on Saturday dawn. The police suspect that he was murdered over previous enmity. The murdered, Hossain Shikdar (50) was the son of late Tamij Uddin. He was killed in his own house. No one was arrested till 1pm for the murder. Officer in charge of Dhunat Police Station Yasin Ali told bdnews24.com that Hossain was sleeping in his house on Friday night. At around 4am Saturday, criminals cut through the corrugated sheet wall and slaughtered him with sharp weapons in his sleep, said Yasin. At this time, the family of Hossain awoke and started crying as they found him. The assailants had fled by the time neighbours came out hearing the cries. Police recovered the body and sent it to Shaheed Ziaur Rahman Medical College Hospital for post mortem, added Yasin. bdnew
